# Environment Variables Template

## For Local Development
Create a `.env` file in the project root with:

```env
# Backend Environment
DEBUG=true
ALLOW_CORS_ALL=true
DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///./hrms.db
CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://localhost:5173,http://127.0.0.1:5173
```

## For Production on Render

Set these in Render Dashboard → Environment Variables:

```
DATABASE_URL = postgresql://user:password@your-db-host/hrms_db
CORS_ORIGINS = https://your-domain.vercel.app
ALLOW_CORS_ALL = false
DEBUG = false
```

## For Production on Vercel (Frontend)

Set these in Vercel Dashboard → Settings → Environment Variables:

```
VITE_API_URL = https://your-backend-api.onrender.com
```

## Important Notes

- **Never commit `.env` files** to Git
- Use `.env.example` to show required variables
- DATABASE_URL: Create PostgreSQL database on Render and copy connection string
- CORS_ORIGINS: Must match your frontend domain exactly
- VITE_API_URL: Must match your Render backend URL exactly
